segment/scan/pending.description: Number of segments in queue waiting to be scanned.

ingest/events/thrownAway.description: Number of events rejected because they are outside the windowPeriod.

ingest/events/unparseable.description: Number of events rejected because the events are unparseable.

ingest/events/duplicate.description: Number of events rejected because the events are duplicated.

ingest/events/processed.description: Number of events successfully processed per emission period.

ingest/persists/cpu.description: Cpu time in Nanoseconds spent on doing intermediate persist.

ingest/persists/backPressure.description: Milliseconds spent creating persist tasks and blocking waiting for them to finish.

ingest/handoff/count.description: Number of times handoff has happened.

ingest/merge/cpu.description: Cpu time in Nanoseconds spent on merging intermediate segments.

ingest/events/messageGap.description: Time gap between the data time in event and current system time.

segment/assigned/count.description: Number of segments assigned to be loaded in the cluster.

segment/moved/count.description: Number of segments assigned to be loaded in the cluster.

segment/dropped/count.description: Number of segments dropped due to being overshadowed.

segment/deleted/count.description: Number of segments dropped due to rules.

segment/unneeded/count.description: Number of segments dropped due to being marked as unused.

segment/loadQueue/size.description: Size in bytes of segments to load.

segment/loadQueue/failed.description: Number of segments that failed to load.

segment/size.description: Size in bytes of available segments.

segment/unavailable/count.description: Number of segments (not including replicas) left to load until segments that should be loaded in the cluster are available for queries.

segment/underReplicated/count.description: Number of segments (including replicas) left to load until segments that should be loaded in the cluster are available for queries.

tier/historical/count.description: Number of available historical nodes in each tier.

tier/replication/factor.description: Configured maximum replication factor in each tier.

tier/required/capacity.description: Total capacity in bytes required in each tier.

tier/total/capacity.description: Total capacity in bytes available in each tier.

ingest/kafka/lag.description: Total lag between the offsets consumed by the Kafka indexing tasks and latest offsets in Kafka brokers across all partitions.

ingest/kafka/maxLag.description: Max lag between the offsets consumed by the Kafka indexing tasks and latest offsets in Kafka brokers across all partitions.

ingest/kafka/avgLag.description: Average lag between the offsets consumed by the Kafka indexing tasks and latest offsets in Kafka brokers across all partitions.

task/success/count.description: Number of successful tasks per emission period.

task/failed/count.description: Number of failed tasks per emission period.

task/run/time.description: Milliseconds taken to run a task.

task/action/log/time.description: Milliseconds taken to log a task action to the audit log.

task/action/run/time.description: Milliseconds taken to execute a task action.
